<i>adjective</i>: 휑하다 [휑하다], 훤하다 [훤ː하다], 환하다 [환ː하다], 해박하다 [해바카다], 유식하다 [유ː시카다], 박학하다 [바카카다], 박식하다 [박씨카다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adjective</i><br>
<dt>휑하다 [휑하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. familiar; knowledgeable</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 것에 대해 매우 잘 알아 매우 환하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having an accurate and deep knowledge of a certain task or object.</dd><br>
<dd>2. open; clear</dd><br>
<dd>구멍 등이 막힌 데 없이 시원하게 나 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>Something such as a hole, being widely open, being unblocked.</dd><br>
<dd>3. empty; lonely</dd><br>
<dd>속이 비고 넓어서 매우 허전하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Being wide and empty, making one feel lonely.</dd><br>
<dd>4. sunken; hollow</dd><br>
<dd>눈이 쑥 들어가 있고 생기가 없다.</dd><br>
<dd>Eyes being sunken and lifeless.</dd><br>
<dt>훤하다 [훤ː하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. bright; light</dd><br>
<dd>조금 흐릿하게 밝다.</dd><br>
<dd>Being slightly, dimly bright.</dd><br>
<dd>2. open; clear</dd><br>
<dd>앞이 탁 트여 매우 넓고 시원스럽다.</dd><br>
<dd>A view being sweeping and unobstructed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. clear; obvious</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일의 내용이나 사정이 확실하고 분명하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Something being transparent, obvious or quite predictable.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fine-looking; attractive-looking</dd><br>
<dd>외모가 잘생겨 보기에 매우 시원스럽다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having an extremely pleasing, neat, attractive appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>5. familiar; knowledgeable</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이나 대상에 대해 잘 알고 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having an accurate and deep knowledge about a certain task or object.</dd><br>
<dt>환하다 [환ː하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. bright; light; radiant</dd><br>
<dd>빛이 비치어 맑고 밝다.</dd><br>
<dd>Being very clear and bright as light shines.</dd><br>
<dd>2. open; clear</dd><br>
<dd>앞이 탁 트여 넓고 시원스럽다.</dd><br>
<dd>Something imparting a feeling of not being confined, because it has an open view.</dd><br>
<dd>3. clear; obvious</dd><br>
<dd>무슨 일이 되어 가는 사정이나 속내가 분명하다.</dd><br>
<dd>The progress or intention of a certain event being clear.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fine-looking; attractive-looking</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴이 깔끔하게 잘생겨 보기에 좋다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having a pleasing, neat, and attractive appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>5. bright; beaming; radiant</dd><br>
<dd>표정이나 성격이 명랑하고 밝다.</dd><br>
<dd>One's face or personality being bright and cheerful.</dd><br>
<dd>6. bright; light</dd><br>
<dd>색이 밝고 맑다.</dd><br>
<dd>Color being bright and clear.</dd><br>
<dd>7. familiar; knowledgeable</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이나 대상에 대해 잘 알고 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having an accurate and deep knowledge about a certain task or object.</dd><br>
<dd>8. refreshed</dd><br>
<dd>맛이 얼얼한 듯하면서 개운하고 시원한 느낌이 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>Feeling tingly, clean, and refreshed in one's mouth</dd><br>
<dt>해박하다 [해바카다]</dt><br>
<dd>knowledgeable; erudite; learned</dd><br>
<dd>여러 방면으로 학식이 넓고 아는 것이 많다.</dd><br>
<dd>Being learned and having a lot of knowledge in many areas.</dd><br>
<dt>유식하다 [유ː시카다]</dt><br>
<dd>knowledgeable; intelligent</dd><br>
<dd>배워서 아는 것이 많다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having much knowledge from learning.</dd><br>
<dt>박학하다 [바카카다]</dt><br>
<dd>erudite; knowledgeable</dd><br>
<dd>배운 것이 많고 학문의 지식이 넓다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having gained a lot of knowledge through study.</dd><br>
<dt>박식하다 [박씨카다]</dt><br>
<dd>knowledgeable; erudite</dd><br>
<dd>아는 것이 매우 많다.</dd><br>
<dd>Having a lot of knowledge.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>